text.tspan: Hackers aren't wizards. They use simple methods
to steal information and money. Simple steps can
stop them. Here's what you should do.
twofactorauth.org - Instructions for enabling two-step verification
Change your passwords and check any financial and privacy settings.
Run a malware scan on your computer or phone.
Perform a factory reset if you discover your computer was compromised.

flowRoot.flowPara: Skip links and files in suspicious emails. Instead, go to the official website directly, or contact the sender outside of email to verify that the message is legit.
Enable two-step verification to make sure you can get into your accounts, not just someone who has your password. Learn more at twofactorauth.org.
Use a password manager to create and keep track of unique passwords for all of your accounts.
Use automatic updates for your devices and software. Reboot your system weekly so the updates can take effect.
Backup your data to a drive or service that isn't always connected. That way, if your data is stolen, deleted or ransomed you will still have a copy.

text.tspan: haveibeenpwned.com - See if your account has been breached

flowRoot.flowPara: Pick 4-5 letters at random, then choose an interesting word that starts with each
Arrange the words into a phrase you can remember.
